@startuml
title EduSecure - Submission AES-at-Rest and Lecturer Retrieval

actor Student
actor "Assignment-owning Lecturer" as Lecturer
actor Admin
participant Browser
participant "SubmissionController" as Controller
participant "SubmissionService" as Service
participant "AesRsaCryptoService\n(hash/sign/verify/audit HMAC)" as Crypto
participant "SubmissionContentEncryptionService\n(AES-GCM)" as ContentCrypto
participant "SubmissionKeyProtectionService\n(AESWrap)" as KeyProtection
database "SubmissionRepository\n(PostgreSQL)" as SubmissionRepo
collections "FileSystemSubmissionContentStore\n(default ./var/submission-storage)" as FileStore
participant "AuditService" as Audit

== Student submission ==

Student -> Browser : choose TXT or PDF file
Browser -> Controller : POST /api/assignments/{assignmentId}/submissions\nauthenticated session-cookie request\n(HTTPS in intended deployment)
Controller -> Service : createSubmission(currentUserEmail, assignmentId, file)
Service -> Service : verify assignment is visible\nthrough current student space membership

Service -> Service : validate file\n- filename\n- size\n- content type\n- UTF-8/PDF checks
Service -> Service : read plaintext file bytes

== Integrity and authorship on plaintext ==

Service -> Crypto : hash(plaintext bytes)
Crypto --> Service : SHA-256 digest

Service -> Crypto : sign(digest bytes)
Crypto --> Service : digitalSignature

Service -> Crypto : verify(digest bytes, digitalSignature)
Crypto --> Service : verificationStatus

== AES at rest ==

Service -> ContentCrypto : encrypt(plaintext bytes)
activate ContentCrypto
ContentCrypto -> ContentCrypto : generate random AES-256 DEK
ContentCrypto -> ContentCrypto : generate random 12-byte GCM nonce
ContentCrypto -> ContentCrypto : encrypt with AES/GCM/NoPadding
ContentCrypto --> Service : ciphertext + Base64 nonce\n+ algorithm + DEK
deactivate ContentCrypto

Service -> KeyProtection : wrap(DEK)
activate KeyProtection
KeyProtection -> KeyProtection : load submission.storage.master-key
KeyProtection -> KeyProtection : wrap DEK using AESWrap
KeyProtection --> Service : wrappedContentEncryptionKey\n+ keyWrapAlgorithm + storageKeyVersion
deactivate KeyProtection

Service -> FileStore : store(ciphertext)
FileStore --> Service : storedFileReference\nsubmission://<uuid>.bin

Service -> SubmissionRepo : save Submission\nmetadata + encrypted-at-rest fields\n+ digest/signature/verification fields
SubmissionRepo --> Service : saved submission

Service -> Audit : record(SUBMISSION_CREATED)
Audit --> Service : audit recorded

alt verification succeeds
    Service -> Audit : record(SUBMISSION_VERIFIED)
    Audit --> Service : audit recorded
else verification fails but submission is retained
    Service -> Audit : record(SUBMISSION_VERIFICATION_FAILED)
    Audit --> Service : audit recorded
end

Service --> Controller : SubmissionResponse\n(metadata only)
Controller --> Browser : 201 Created

note right of FileStore
Disk stores ciphertext only.
Plaintext file bytes are not stored directly.
The path shown here is the default configured base path,
not a hard-coded deployment guarantee.
end note

note right of SubmissionRepo
DB stores the reference and decryption metadata:
- storedFileReference
- storageEncryptionNonce
- wrappedContentEncryptionKey
- storageKeyVersion
- ciphertextLengthBytes
- hash/signature status
end note

== Lecturer content retrieval ==

Lecturer -> Controller : GET /api/submissions/{submissionId}/content
Controller -> Service : getSubmissionContent(submissionId, authentication)

Service -> Service : requireAccessibleSubmission(...)
note right of Service
Current policy allows:
- owner student while the related assignment remains\n  visible through current space membership
- lecturer who owns the assignment
- admin
Denies unrelated student and unrelated lecturer.
end note

Service -> SubmissionRepo : findById(submissionId)
SubmissionRepo --> Service : submission metadata

Service -> FileStore : read(storedFileReference)
FileStore --> Service : ciphertext bytes

Service -> KeyProtection : unwrap(wrappedContentEncryptionKey, storageKeyVersion)
activate KeyProtection
KeyProtection -> KeyProtection : load master key
KeyProtection -> KeyProtection : unwrap DEK using AESWrap
KeyProtection --> Service : plaintext DEK
deactivate KeyProtection

Service -> ContentCrypto : decrypt(ciphertext, nonce, DEK)
activate ContentCrypto
ContentCrypto -> ContentCrypto : decrypt with AES/GCM/NoPadding
ContentCrypto --> Service : plaintext file bytes
deactivate ContentCrypto

Service -> Audit : record(SUBMISSION_CONTENT_ACCESSED)
Audit --> Service : audit recorded

Service --> Controller : SubmissionContentResponse\n(fileName, contentType, plaintext bytes)
Controller --> Lecturer : 200 OK attachment download

note over Lecturer,Controller
Lecturer does not decrypt locally.
The server decrypts on demand and returns the original file.
end note

Admin -> Controller : GET /api/submissions/{submissionId}/content
Controller -> Service : getSubmissionContent(submissionId, authentication)
Service -> Service : apply admin override
Service --> Controller : SubmissionContentResponse
Controller --> Admin : 200 OK attachment download

note right of Crypto
Despite the legacy class name, `AesRsaCryptoService`
currently signs with `SHA256withECDSA`.

It is not the AES-at-rest file cipher.
It provides:
- SHA-256 hashing
- ECDSA signing and verification
- HMAC-SHA-256 audit integrity
end note

@enduml

